description: This dashboard displays ais metrics that get exposed to Prometheus by the aisexporter.

targets.expr: sum(ais_recent_ships_observed{job="ais", time_period="latest", instance=~"^$instance$"} - ais_recent_ships_with_position{job="ais", time_period="latest", instance=~"^$instance$"})

panels.content:
#### ships
This graph displays the counts of ships (e.g unique ICAO) being reported. ships are grouped into total ships being reported, ships reported with a position, ships reported without a position and ships reported that have multi-lateration reports.

##### Maximum Range
This graph displays the maximum range of the currently observed ships reporting a position.

##### Messages
This graph displays the messages received per second.

##### Signal Strength
This graph displays the signal levels reported for noise, mean and peak signal levels. The values are reported in [dbFS](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DBFS).

##### CPU Utilisation
This graph displays how much CPU time is used by the ais tool. demod reports the time spent demodulating and decoding data from the USB SDR dongle. usb reports time spent reading sample data from the USB SDR dongle. other reports time spent doing network I/O, processing network messages, and periodic tasks.

title: aisexporter
